The paper deals with the problem of gathering in a network with Byzantine agents, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and network algorithms (cs.DS). The use of synchronous rounds and communication constraints also suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY). The algorithms designed in the paper involve decision-making and label manipulation, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT).
